legacy.full_text: I am glad to join the virtual conference tonight and share with everyone my thoughts on future China-US relations. Stay tuned at 8 pm EST

It is our firm belief that China and the United States can benefit from the prosperity and development of the other side. We may have competition, but we don’t have to be rivals. Instead, we should strive to be partners. Read my speech at the event: https://t.co/VWS32fPbg1 https://t.co/twoRYj8z6o

legacy.description: Former Chinese Ambassador to the US
legacy.name: Cui Tiankai

legacy.full_text: Our two countries have not a small number of differences and disagreements. The only way out of them is candid and equal-footed dialogue on the basis of mutual respect. Claiming that dialogue is useless is no less than advocating confrontation.

legacy.description: Former Chinese Ambassador to the US
legacy.name: Cui Tiankai

legacy.full_text: On issues that concern its sovereignty, reunification and territorial integrity, China will not back down, and it is hoped that the U.S. side will respect China’s core interests and refrain from crossing the red line.
